article:
'Hansen' is a Danish-Norwegian patronymic surname, literally meaning son of
[[Hans (name)|Hans]]. It is the third most common surname in Denmark, shared by
about 4.3% of the
population. [http://www.dst.dk/Statistik/Navne/pop/2008.aspx] Statistics
Denmark Hansen is the single most common surname in Norway, not counting
spelling variations such as Hanssen, which are also quite
common. [http://www.ssb.no/emner/00/navn/index.html] Statistics Norway
In the Faroe Islands Hansen is the second most common surname, while in the
North German federal states of Schleswig-Holstein and Hamburg Hansen is the
third and fifth most common surname,
respectively. [http://www.verwandt.de/karten/absolut/hansen.html Map of
German telephone directory entries] In Sweden the parallel form is
[[Hanson (surname)|Hansson]]. The frequent occurrences of Hansen as a surname
outside
Denmark, [http://www.danskernesnavne.navneforskning.ku.dk/Personnavne.asp
University of Copenhagen - Name Research Section] Norway and Schleswig-
Holstein is due to immigration, though immigrants to English-speaking countries
often changed the spelling to match the English lastname: Hanson in order to
accommodate English orthographic rules.
